**Power Rangers** is an American entertainment and merchandising
[franchise](/wiki/Media_franchise "Media franchise") built around a live
action superhero television series. Produced first by [Saban
Entertainment](/wiki/Saban_Entertainment "Saban Entertainment"), later by [BVS
Entertainment](/wiki/BVS_Entertainment "BVS Entertainment"), and today by [SCG
Power Rangers](/wiki/SCG_Power_Rangers "SCG Power Rangers"), the television
series takes much of its [footage](/wiki/Footage "Footage") from the Japanese
[tokusatsu](/wiki/Tokusatsu "Tokusatsu") _[Super Sentai](/wiki/Super_Sentai
"Super Sentai")_ , produced by [Toei Company](/wiki/Toei_Company "Toei
Company").[1] The first _Power Rangers_ entry, _[Mighty Morphin Power
Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_ ,
debuted on August 28, 1993, and helped launch the [Fox Kids](/wiki/Fox_Kids
"Fox Kids") programming block of the 1990s, during which it catapulted into
[popular culture](/wiki/Popular_culture "Popular culture") along with a line
of [action figures](/wiki/Action_figure "Action figure") and other toys by
[Bandai](/wiki/Bandai "Bandai").[2] As of
2001[[update]](//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Power_Rangers&action=edit),
the media franchise has generated over $6 billion in retail sales
worldwide.[3]

Despite initial
[criticism](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers#Reception_and_controversy
"Mighty Morphin Power Rangers") that its action violence targeted child
audiences, the franchise has continued, and as of
2017[[update]](//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Power_Rangers&action=edit)
the show consists of 24 television seasons of 20 different themed series and
three theatrical films released in 1995, 1997 and 2017. In 2010, [Haim
Saban](/wiki/Haim_Saban "Haim Saban"), creator of the series, regained
ownership of the franchise after seven years under [The Walt Disney
Company](/wiki/The_Walt_Disney_Company "The Walt Disney Company").

## Premise

Further information: [List of Power Rangers
characters](/wiki/List_of_Power_Rangers_characters "List of Power Rangers
characters") and [List of Power Rangers
villains](/wiki/List_of_Power_Rangers_villains "List of Power Rangers
villains")

Since _Power Rangers_ derives most of its footage from the _[Super
Sentai](/wiki/Super_Sentai "Super Sentai")_ series, it features many
[hallmarks](/wiki/Super_Sentai#Common_elements "Super Sentai") that
distinguish it from other superhero series. Each series revolves around a team
of youths recruited and trained by a mentor to morph into the eponymous Power
Rangers, able to utilize special powers and pilot immense assault machines,
called Zords, to overcome the periodic antagonists. In the original series
_Mighty Morphin_ , the wizard [Zordon](/wiki/Zordon "Zordon") recruits
"[teenagers](/wiki/Teenagers "Teenagers") with attitude" against [Rita
Repulsa](/wiki/Rita_Repulsa "Rita Repulsa").[4]

When "morphed," the rangers become powerful [superheroes](/wiki/Superhero
"Superhero") wearing color-coded skin-tight [spandex](/wiki/Spandex "Spandex")
suits and helmets with [opaque](/wiki/Opacity_\(optics\) "Opacity \(optics\)")
[visors](/wiki/Visor "Visor"); identical except in individual rangers' color
and helmet design. Morphed Rangers generally possess enhanced strength,
durability, agility and combat prowess. Some possess superhuman or
[psychic](/wiki/Psychic "Psychic") abilities such as super-speed, element
manipulation, [extra-sensory perception](/wiki/Extra-sensory_perception
"Extra-sensory perception") or [invisibility](/wiki/Invisibility
"Invisibility").[5] In addition, each individual ranger has a unique
[weapon](/wiki/Weapon "Weapon"), as well as common weaponry used for ground
fighting.[note 1] When enemies grow to incredible size (as nearly all do),
Rangers utilize individual Zords that combine into a larger Megazord.

Rangers teams operate in teams of five or three, with more Rangers joining the
team later. Each team of Rangers, with a few exceptions, obeys a general set
of conventions, outlined at the beginning of _Mighty Morphin_ and implied by
mentors throughout many of the other series: Power Rangers may not use their
Ranger powers for personal gain or for escalating a fight (unless the enemy
does so), nor may the Power Rangers disclose their identities to the general
public.[note 2] The penalty for disobeying these rules, in _[Mighty Morphin
Power Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Power
Rangers")_ , is the loss of their power.

As in _Super Sentai_ , the color palette of each _Power Rangers_ team changes
every series.[note 3] Only Red and Blue appear in every Ranger team, while a
Yellow Ranger has been present in every season except _[Power Rangers Dino
Charge](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Dino_Charge "Power Rangers Dino Charge")_. Other
colors and designations also appear throughout the series.[note 4] A Rangers'
color designation also influences their wardrobe throughout the series:
civilian clothing often matches Ranger color.[note 5]

## History

### Adapting the _Super Sentai_ series

Production of _Power Rangers_ episodes involves extensive localization of and
revision of original _Super Sentai_ source material in order to incorporate
American culture and conform to American television standards. Rather than
making an English [dub](/wiki/Dubbing_\(filmmaking\) "Dubbing \(filmmaking\)")
or [translation](/wiki/Translation "Translation") of the Japanese footage,
_Power Rangers_ programs consist of scenes featuring [English-
speaking](/wiki/English_Language "English Language") actors (either from the
[United States](/wiki/United_States "United States"), [Canada](/wiki/Canada
"Canada"), [Australia](/wiki/Australia "Australia"), [New
Zealand](/wiki/New_Zealand "New Zealand"), or the [United
Kingdom](/wiki/United_Kingdom "United Kingdom")) spliced with scenes featuring
either Japanese actors dubbed into English or the action scenes from the Super
Sentai Series featuring the Rangers fighting [monsters](/wiki/Kaiju "Kaiju")
or the [giant robot](/wiki/Mecha "Mecha") (Zord and Megazord) battles with
English dubbing. In some series, original fight scenes are filmed to
incorporate characters or items unique to the _Power Rangers_ production.[6]
Like many of [Saban Entertainment](/wiki/Saban_Entertainment "Saban
Entertainment") previous ventures in [localizing](/wiki/Language_localisation
"Language localisation") Japanese television for a
[Western](/wiki/Western_culture "Western culture") audience, the plot,
character names, and other names usually differ greatly from the source
footage, though a few seasons have stayed close to the story of the original
Super Sentai season.

Along with adapting the villains from the Super Sentai counterparts, most
_Power Rangers_ series also feature villains with no Sentai counterpart.
Generally, the primary antagonist of a _Power Rangers_ series (for example,
Lord Zedd, Divatox, etc.) are not adapted from the Sentai. Exceptions to this
includes _Mighty Morphin_ , _Zeo_ , _Lightspeed Rescue_ and a few others which
only use villains adapted from the Japanese shows.

The series that began the [franchise](/wiki/Media_franchise "Media
franchise"), _[Mighty Morphin Power
Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_
(an American adaptation of the 1992 Japanese [Super Sentai](/wiki/Super_Sentai
"Super Sentai") Series, _[Kyōryū Sentai
Zyuranger](/wiki/Ky%C5%8Dry%C5%AB_Sentai_Zyuranger "Kyōryū Sentai
Zyuranger")_), began broadcasting as part of the [Fox Kids](/wiki/Fox_Kids
"Fox Kids") block of programing that aired on the
[FOX](/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company "Fox Broadcasting Company") network. It
lasted for three seasons (from 1993 to 1996).[7]

### Broadcast history

[![](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/01/Power_rangers.png/250px-
Power_rangers.png)](/wiki/File:Power_rangers.png)

[](/wiki/File:Power_rangers.png "Enlarge")

The Saban Entertainment run of the franchise—beginning with _[Power Rangers in
Space](/wiki/Power_Rangers_in_Space "Power Rangers in Space")_ —used this
version of the _Power Rangers_ logo (1998–2001).

[Saban Entertainment](/wiki/Saban_Entertainment "Saban Entertainment")
distributed the _Power Rangers_ series from 1993 until the end of 2001, and
Fox broadcast it until the [fall](/wiki/Autumn "Autumn") of 2002. [The Walt
Disney Company](/wiki/The_Walt_Disney_Company "The Walt Disney Company")
purchased the franchise as part of a buyout that took place in
2001.[7][8][9][10] This resulted in Fox Family Worldwide becoming [ABC Family
Worldwide Inc.](/wiki/ABC_Family_Worldwide_Inc. "ABC Family Worldwide
Inc.")[10] This buyout also saw Saban Entertainment becoming BVS Entertainment
in 2002, from [News Corporation](/wiki/News_Corporation "News Corporation"),
Fox's parent company, and [Haim Saban](/wiki/Haim_Saban "Haim Saban").[10] The
show continued to air on Fox until the company replaced its [Fox
Kids](/wiki/Fox_Kids "Fox Kids") package with "FoxBox" in the United States.
Since September 2002, all _Power Rangers_ shows had aired on various Disney-
owned networks ([ABC Kids](/wiki/ABC_Kids_\(United_States\) "ABC Kids \(United
States\)"), [Toon Disney](/wiki/Toon_Disney "Toon Disney") and
[Jetix](/wiki/Jetix "Jetix") channels worldwide).[7] When _[Wild
Force](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Wild_Force "Power Rangers Wild Force")_ ended,
Disney moved production of the franchise from Los Angeles to New Zealand. This
resulted in the closure of MMPR Productions and the dismissal of many members
of the production. From _[Ninja Storm](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Ninja_Storm "Power
Rangers Ninja Storm")_ to date, _Power Rangers_ is produced in New Zealand.
ABC Family, another Disney-owned network, also used to air _Power Rangers_
until it did away with its Jetix timeslot after August 31, 2006. On February
12, 2009, Toon Disney ended in the wake of [Disney XD](/wiki/Disney_XD "Disney
XD"), ending cable airings of _Power Rangers_ in certain areas of the United
States. Several ABC affiliate broadcasting groups declined to air most of the
_Power Rangers_ series since 2006 due to the lack of FCC-compliant
[educational and informational content](/wiki/E/I "E/I") in the programs.[11]

The Saban era seasons, starting with _In Space_ , have gone under the "Saban's
Power Rangers" moniker, up until _Time Force_. Since the re-acquisition of
_Power Rangers_ by Saban in 2010, this practice has continued once again
starting with _Samurai_.

Starting in 2005, up until 2007, during its run on Jetix, _Power Rangers_
reruns were aired under the moniker _Power Rangers Generations_ , showcasing
select episodes from _Mighty Morphin_ through _Dino Thunder_.

An article in _[The New Zealand Herald](/wiki/The_New_Zealand_Herald "The New
Zealand Herald")_ published on March 7, 2009, identified _[Power Rangers
RPM](/wiki/Power_Rangers_RPM "Power Rangers RPM")_ as the last season of the
_Power Rangers_ run. Production manager Sally Campbell stated in an interview,
"...at this stage we will not be shooting another season."[12][13] A September
1, 2009, revision to _[Disney A to Z: The Official
Encyclopedia](/wiki/Disney_A_to_Z:_The_Official_Encyclopedia "Disney A to Z:
The Official Encyclopedia")_ by Disney's head archivist [Dave
Smith](/wiki/Dave_Smith_\(archivist\) "Dave Smith \(archivist\)") states that
"production of new episodes [of _Power Rangers_] ceased in 2009".[14]
Production of _Power Rangers_ ceased and the
last[[update]](//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Power_Rangers&action=edit)
series by BVS Entertainment, _RPM_ , ended on December 26, 2009.[12]

On October 1, 2009, Bandai released a press release that Disney would re-
broadcast _[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers
"Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_ starting in January 2010 on [ABC
Kids](/wiki/ABC_Kids_\(United_States\) "ABC Kids \(United States\)") in lieu
of a new series utilizing footage from the [2009 _Super Sentai_ television
series](/wiki/Samurai_Sentai_Shinkenger "Samurai Sentai Shinkenger"). A new
toy line accompanied the series and appeared in stores in the later part of
2009.[7][15][16] ABC's over-the air telecasts ended on August 28, 2010, and
turned the hour back to affiliates.

On May 12, 2010, [Haim Saban](/wiki/Haim_Saban "Haim Saban") bought back the
_Power Rangers_ franchise from Disney for $43 million and announced plans to
produce a new season of the television series.[17][18][19] The eighteenth
season, _[Samurai](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Samurai "Power Rangers Samurai")_ ,
began airing on [Nickelodeon](/wiki/Nickelodeon "Nickelodeon") on February 7,
2011,[18][20] with the previous episodes beginning rebroadcast on
[Nicktoons](/wiki/Nicktoons_\(TV_channel\) "Nicktoons \(TV channel\)") later
that year.[20][21][22] It was also announced that Saban plans to make a new
Power Rangers movie.[23]

On July 2, 2012, it was announced that [Saban
Brands](/wiki/Saban_Capital_Group "Saban Capital Group") would launch a
[Saturday morning cartoon](/wiki/Saturday_morning_cartoon "Saturday morning
cartoon") block on [The CW](/wiki/The_CW_Television_Network "The CW Television
Network"), called [Vortexx](/wiki/Vortexx "Vortexx"), on August 25, 2012, that
would air _Power Rangers Lost Galaxy_.[24][25][26][27][28] To commemorate the
series' 20th anniversary, Nickelodeon began airing _[Power Rangers
Megaforce](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Megaforce "Power Rangers Megaforce")_ on
February 2, 2013, featuring all of the past rangers from the series' 20-year
history. On October 1, 2013, Saban Brands announced that it had extended
agreements with Nickelodeon and Bandai America Incorporated through 2016 for
its globally recognized Power Rangers franchise.[29] In January 2016, Saban
and Nickelodeon extended their broadcast partnership through 2018.[30]

[The 90s Are All That](/wiki/The_90s_Are_All_That "The 90s Are All That")
aired _[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers
"Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_ as part of Mighty Morphin Weekend in 2013.

Variations of Power Rangers throughout the franchise unite.

The first series _Mighty Morphin Power Rangers_ through _In Space_ followed a
[story arc](/wiki/Story_arc "Story arc") called "The Zordon Era" with a
gradually changing cast and characters over six years. Beginning with _Lost
Galaxy_ , although it had ties with the previous story arc, each _Power
Rangers_ series had its own self-contained
[storylines](/wiki/Plot_\(narrative\) "Plot \(narrative\)"), independent of
previous series. [Crossover](/wiki/Fictional_crossover "Fictional crossover")
episodes between different series featuring rangers, villains, and other
characters from past seasons also began with _Lost Galaxy_ , with a few
exceptions.

### The Saban Era

The Saban Era is seasons 1-10 that includes _[Mighty Morphin Power
Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_
(1993-1996) to _[Power Rangers Wild Force](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Wild_Force
"Power Rangers Wild Force")_ (2002). These series aired on
[Fox](/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company "Fox Broadcasting Company") during the
[Fox Kids](/wiki/Fox_Kids "Fox Kids") programming block. The Zordon Era is
_[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty
Morphin Power Rangers")_ to _[Power Rangers in
Space](/wiki/Power_Rangers_in_Space "Power Rangers in Space")_.

  * _[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers")_ (1993–1996) 
    * Season 1: When the evil witch [Rita Repulsa](/wiki/Rita_Repulsa "Rita Repulsa") and her minions [Goldar](/wiki/Goldar "Goldar"), Squatt, Baboo, and Finster, are freed from their imprisonment on the Moon, the wizard [Zordon](/wiki/Zordon "Zordon"), with the help of his assistant [Alpha 5](/wiki/Alpha_5_\(Power_Rangers\) "Alpha 5 \(Power Rangers\)"), enlists five teenagers—[Jason Lee Scott](/wiki/Jason_Lee_Scott "Jason Lee Scott"), [Trini Kwan](/wiki/Trini_Kwan "Trini Kwan"), [Billy Cranston](/wiki/Billy_Cranston "Billy Cranston"), [Kimberly Hart](/wiki/Kimberly_Hart "Kimberly Hart"), and [Zack Taylor](/wiki/Zack_Taylor "Zack Taylor")—to become the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers to battle Rita's invasion of the Earth, using their Power Coins and Dinozords to combat her monsters. Rita soon creates her own evil Power Ranger by brainwashing a recent transfer student [Tommy Oliver](/wiki/Tommy_Oliver "Tommy Oliver"), but the Power Rangers are able to free him from her control and he joins their side. This season uses footage from _[Kyōryu Sentai Zyuranger](/wiki/Ky%C5%8Dryu_Sentai_Zyuranger "Kyōryu Sentai Zyuranger")_.
    * Season 2: Rita's superior [Lord Zedd](/wiki/Lord_Zedd "Lord Zedd") returns to the Earth to take over for Rita's incompetence, imprisoning her once more. His new monsters prove too powerful for the Dinozords, leading Zordon to empower them into the Thunderzords. Jason, Trini, and Zack leave to join a youth conference in Switzerland, and are replaced by Rocky DeSantos, Aisha Campbell, and [Adam Park](/wiki/Adam_Park "Adam Park"), respectively, and Rita returns and marries Lord Zedd. This season uses footage from _[Gosei Sentai Dairanger](/wiki/Gosei_Sentai_Dairanger "Gosei Sentai Dairanger")_.
    * _[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: The Movie](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Power_Rangers:_The_Movie "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: The Movie")_ (1995): When the evil wizard [Ivan Ooze](/wiki/Ivan_Ooze "Ivan Ooze") is freed by construction work, he takes revenge against Zordon for imprisoning him. As his powers are too strong for the Power Rangers, Alpha 5 uses the last of the Command Center's power to send them to the planet Phaedos to learn the ways of the Ninjetti from the warrior Dulcea to stop Ooze before he can conquer the universe. The movie, which does not fall into the canon of the TV series, drew inspiration from _[Ninja Sentai Kakuranger](/wiki/Ninja_Sentai_Kakuranger "Ninja Sentai Kakuranger")_.
    * Season 3: Rita's brother [Rito Revolto](/wiki/Rito_Revolto "Rito Revolto") comes to Earth and destroys the Power Rangers' Power Coins and Thunderzords. The Power Rangers seek out [Ninjor](/wiki/Ninjor_\(Power_Rangers\) "Ninjor \(Power Rangers\)"), creator of the Power Coins, for new Power Coins giving them new ninja powers and the Ninjazords, and later the Shogunzords. Rita also enchants a new Australian exchange student Kat Hillard into slowly draining Kimberly of her Ranger powers, until the spell is broken; when Kimberly ultimately leaves to train for the Olympics, she entrusts Kat to be her replacement amongst the Power Rangers. This season uses footage from _[Ninja Sentai Kakuranger](/wiki/Ninja_Sentai_Kakuranger "Ninja Sentai Kakuranger")_.
    * _[Mighty Morphin Alien Rangers](/wiki/Mighty_Morphin_Alien_Rangers "Mighty Morphin Alien Rangers")_ (1996): When Rita's father Master Vile comes to Earth, he turns back time, turning the Power Rangers, and many of their friends, into children. Zordon calls upon his proteges the Alien Rangers of Aquitar to protect the Earth from Master Vile's monsters and to help work on a machine that would return the child rangers to their proper ages. Unfortunately, Only Billy returns to normal as the machine which required the power coins as a power source is stolen by Rito & Goldar allowing Rita & Zedd to destroy the coins. The child rangers then travel throughout time to gather the fragments of the Zeo Crystal to bring time back to normal. During her journey in Africa, Aisha meets Tanya Sloan and realizes that she can do more help to stop the sickness plaguing the wildlife and sends Tanya back with her Zeo Crystal. This series also uses footage from _[Ninja Sentai Kakuranger](/wiki/Ninja_Sentai_Kakuranger "Ninja Sentai Kakuranger")_.
  * _[Power Rangers Zeo](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Zeo "Power Rangers Zeo")_ (1996): With the Zeo Crystal restored, time brought back to normal, and Master Vile defeated, the Rangers are caught off guard when Goldar and Rito destroy their headquarters. Although Zordon reveals he is fine, he warns the Rangers that the [Machine Empire](/wiki/Machine_Empire "Machine Empire") is planning on conquering the Earth, and the Rangers must use the power of the Zeo Crystal to become the Zeo Rangers to battle them. Billy, who used his scientific prowess to return to his original age during _Alien Rangers_ , decides to work on the Zeo Zords and other machinery, and his presence in the destruction of the previous Command Center leaves him unable to receive the powers of the Gold Ranger, [Trey of Triforia](/wiki/Trey_of_Triforia "Trey of Triforia"), but Jason returns instead. Billy soon begins to age rapidly, a side effect from the regenerator, he used to return to his normal age, and leaves Earth to be healed on Aquitar. This season uses footage from _[Chōriki Sentai Ohranger](/wiki/Ch%C5%8Driki_Sentai_Ohranger "Chōriki Sentai Ohranger")_.
  * _[Turbo: A Power Rangers Movie](/wiki/Turbo:_A_Power_Rangers_Movie "Turbo: A Power Rangers Movie")_ (1997): The intergalactic pirate [Divatox](/wiki/Divatox "Divatox") kidnaps the wizard Lerigot to open a dimensional barrier so she can wed the demon Maligore. To stop her, Zordon gives the Rangers their new Turbo Ranger powers to stop her. Rocky, however, has been hurt, and in his stead Zordon sends [Justin Stewart](/wiki/Justin_Stewart "Justin Stewart"), a young boy who inadvertently discovers the Rangers' identities. This film drew inspiration from _[Gekisou Sentai Carranger](/wiki/Gekisou_Sentai_Carranger "Gekisou Sentai Carranger")_ and serves as a bridge to the subsequent TV season.
  * _[Power Rangers Turbo](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Turbo "Power Rangers Turbo")_ (1997): After Divatox's plans are foiled, she sets her sights on conquering the Earth, with the Turbo Rangers and eventually the intergalactic police officer the [Blue Senturion](/wiki/Blue_Senturion "Blue Senturion") combatting her monsters. Tommy, Adam, Tanya, and Kat soon retire from being Power Rangers, choosing [T.J. Johnson](/wiki/T.J._Johnson "T.J. Johnson"), [Carlos Vallerte](/wiki/Carlos_Vallerte "Carlos Vallerte"), [Ashley Hammond](/wiki/Ashley_Hammond "Ashley Hammond"), and [Cassie Chan](/wiki/Cassie_Chan "Cassie Chan") as their replacements, who are also assisted by the [Phantom Ranger](/wiki/Phantom_Ranger "Phantom Ranger"). Zordon also leaves, putting [Dimitria](/wiki/Dimitria "Dimitria") in his place. This season uses footage from _[Gekisou Sentai Carranger](/wiki/Gekisou_Sentai_Carranger "Gekisou Sentai Carranger")_.
  * _[Power Rangers in Space](/wiki/Power_Rangers_in_Space "Power Rangers in Space")_ (1998): After Divatox succeeds in destroying the Command Center, she is called off planet to participate in Dark Specter's evil alliance in conquering the universe. T.J., Carlos, Ashley, and Cassie travel into outer space to try to stop him, and meet up with [Andros](/wiki/Andros_\(Power_Rangers\) "Andros \(Power Rangers\)"), who they join to become the Space Rangers to stop Dark Specter and his protege [Astronema](/wiki/Astronema "Astronema"). They eventually awaken Andros' friend Zhane, the Silver Ranger, and free Andros' sister [Karone](/wiki/Karone "Karone") (Astronema) from Dark Specter's control and ultimately use Zordon, captured by Dark Specter, to defeat Dark Specter's armies and free the universe from his control. ## Distribution

_Power Rangers_ has long had success in international markets and continues to
air in many countries, with the exception of New Zealand, where the series
filming takes place as of
2009[[update]](//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Power_Rangers&action=edit).
As of 2006, _Power Rangers_ aired at least 65 times a week in more than 40
worldwide markets.[37] Many markets carry or have carried the series on their
respective [Fox](/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company "Fox Broadcasting Company") or
later [Jetix](/wiki/Jetix "Jetix")/[Disney XD](/wiki/Disney_XD "Disney XD")
channels or have syndicated the program on regional children's channels or
blocks, either dubbed into the local language or broadcast in the original
English. Since the 2010 acquisition by Saban Brands, international television
distribution rights for Power Rangers have been managed by [MarVista
Entertainment](/wiki/MarVista_Entertainment "MarVista
Entertainment").[38][39][40]

Broadcast in East Asian territories has been treated differently from in other
international markets due to the prevalence and familiarity of 'the _Super
Sentai_ brand originating in Japan. _Power Rangers_ was briefly banned in
Malaysia for supposedly encouraging the use of drugs because it contained the
word "Morphin'" in its title, which could be associated with
[morphine](/wiki/Morphine "Morphine"). The show eventually aired without the
offending word.[41] In Japan, many _Power Rangers_ television seasons and
movies were dubbed into Japanese for television and video with the voice
actors often pulled from past _Super Sentai_ casts, leading to the English-
dubbed [action sequences](/wiki/Stage_combat "Stage combat") being "re-dubbed"
or "restored" back to Japanese as well. _Power Rangers Mystic Force_ is the
latest season to be broadcast in Japan on [Toei
Channel](/w/index.php?title=Toei_Channel&action=edit&redlink=1 "Toei Channel
\(page does not exist\)") in January 2014, with the _Magiranger_ cast voicing
their counterparts. After broadcast of _Power Rangers_ ended in South Korea
with _Wild Force_ , Bandai of Korea started airing [dubbed _Super Sentai_
series](/wiki/Super_Sentai#South_Korea "Super Sentai") under the _파워레인저_
_(Power Ranger)_ brand on [JEI
TV](/w/index.php?title=JEI_TV&action=edit&redlink=1 "JEI TV \(page does not
exist\)"). Some seasons of _Super Sentai_ broadcast in South Korea have
similarly named titles as their American counterparts, such as _Power Ranger
Dino Thunder_[42] for _Abaranger_ in 2007 and _Power Ranger S.P.D._[43] in
place of _Dekaranger_.

## Broadcast

The series originally aired on [Fox](/wiki/Fox_Broadcasting_Company "Fox
Broadcasting Company")'s children block, [Fox Kids](/wiki/Fox_Kids "Fox Kids")
from 1993-2002. When Disney bought the rights to Power Rangers, it moved to
[ABC](/wiki/American_Broadcasting_Company "American Broadcasting Company")'s
Saturday morning block, [ABC Kids](/wiki/ABC_Kids_\(US\) "ABC Kids \(US\)")
from 2002-2010. During that time, all seasons aired on the [ABC
Family](/wiki/Freeform_\(TV_channel\) "Freeform \(TV channel\)") (now
Freeform) and [Toon Disney](/wiki/Toon_Disney "Toon Disney")'s block
[Jetix](/wiki/Jetix "Jetix"). When Saban bought Power Rangers back, the series
aired new episodes on [Nickelodeon](/wiki/Nickelodeon "Nickelodeon"), while
previous seasons aired on [Nicktoons](/wiki/Nicktoons_\(TV_channel\)
"Nicktoons \(TV channel\)").

## Notes

  1. **Jump up ^** As the series progresses, one or more of the Rangers will usually receive [motorcycles](/wiki/Motorcycle "Motorcycle") for long-distance travel, as well as individual Zords. In many series, a Ranger is also given additional Zords or weapons. In some cases, one Ranger may receive something that other Rangers do not; an example is the [Battlizer](/wiki/Battlizer "Battlizer") given to the Red Ranger of each series since _[Power Rangers in Space](/wiki/Power_Rangers_in_Space "Power Rangers in Space")_ (until _[Operation Overdrive](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Operation_Overdrive "Power Rangers Operation Overdrive")_).
  2. **Jump up ^** Public servants (rescue squad, police officers, etc.) appearing as Rangers disregard this convention in _[Power Rangers Lightspeed Rescue](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Lightspeed_Rescue "Power Rangers Lightspeed Rescue")_ , _[Power Rangers S.P.D.](/wiki/Power_Rangers_S.P.D. "Power Rangers S.P.D.")_ , _[Power Rangers Operation Overdrive](/wiki/Power_Rangers_Operation_Overdrive "Power Rangers Operation Overdrive")_ and _[Power Rangers RPM](/wiki/Power_Rangers_RPM "Power Rangers RPM")_.
  3. **Jump up ^** An original Power Ranger, the [Titanium Ranger](/wiki/Titanium_Ranger "Titanium Ranger"), was created especially for _Lightspeed Rescue_ to add a sixth Power Ranger to the series.
  4. **Jump up ^** Other color designations include [metallic](/wiki/Metal "Metal") colors, violet, and "Shadow", as well as protagonists who have powers and costumes similar to those of the Rangers but are not called "Power Rangers", such as the [Blue Senturion](/wiki/Blue_Senturion "Blue Senturion") and [Koragg the Knight Wolf](/wiki/Koragg_the_Knight_Wolf "Koragg the Knight Wolf").
  5. **Jump up ^** A joke highlighted this correlation in _Dino Thunder_ when [Tommy Oliver](/wiki/Tommy_Oliver "Tommy Oliver") (a former Green Ranger, White Ranger, and Red Ranger) became the new Black Ranger; he said that he had to go shopping because he did not own enough black-colored clothing.
